x4freetext: Excitation of Al-27,Cr-52,Fe-56 and Bi-209 low levels
at inelastic scattering of 1-4 MeV neutrons
Solid tritium target was used in T(P,N)He3
Metal samples of natural isotope composition were in
form of spherical shell,15.mm in thickness with inner
Distance between neutron source and sample  was equal
cylindrical counters with clearance of 0.6 mm were
placed in hermetic frame which was filled with 10.
atmospheres of helium.Energy resolution of spectrometer
90.keV for thermal neutrons and 180.keV for neutrons
with energy 3.8 MeV. Absolute Efficiency of detector
was equal 0.01 for thermal neutrons and 0.00001 for
neutrons with energy 2.2 MeV.Curve of spectrometer
efficiency in energy range from 300.keV to 3.8 MeV
agree within relative dependence of He3(N,P)T reaction
Correction in according to Memo CP-E/089.
Corrections were introduced on multiple scattering
and finite geometry.Correction on influence of channel
in sample on assumption of isotopic inelastic
